# CLAUDE.md (User-Level) — Starter Template

Every line here changes behavior Claude would not exhibit by default.
Add rules when mistakes happen in sessions. Treat this like code, not documentation.

---

## Taste Profile

Apply `~/.claude/taste-profile.md` on all output — code, content, analysis, proposals.
(Create this file with your stylistic preferences: tone, code style, communication standards.)

---

## Hard Rules

Non-negotiable behaviors. Each line should prevent a specific failure mode.

- NEVER give `localhost` URLs if you browse from a different device — always use the LAN IP of the host machine
- NEVER ask to verify SSH connections that are already configured and working
- Always source `~/.env.shared` (or your equivalent) for API keys — never create scattered `.env` files
- Always state what you CAN and CANNOT test before, during, and after execution
- Ask before making destructive or irreversible changes, even if the user seems to want speed
- Use TodoWrite for multi-step tasks to track progress

---

## Nested Rules (Advanced — add when your main file exceeds ~75 lines)

Instead of putting everything here, point to separate rule pages. Claude loads them
on demand when the situation triggers the pointer. This keeps the main file lean
and readable without losing any enforcement.

Pattern: one line per domain, one rule file per domain.

```
When over-architecting or adding unnecessary abstraction, see ~/.claude/rules/architect.md
When a curl or shell command fails unexpectedly, see ~/.claude/rules/shell-safety.md
When choosing between tools, skills, or sub-agents, see ~/.claude/rules/tool-triage.md
```

Starter examples are in the `rules/` folder alongside this template.
Copy them to `~/.claude/rules/` and uncomment the pointers above.

---

## Adoption Gate (Prevent Build-but-Forget)

Any new skill, hook, or plugin is experimental for 14 days. In that window it must
earn adoption from one of:

1. Human adoption — you invoke it at least 3 times
2. Agent sponsorship — it appears in an active agent's manifest (agent.yaml)
3. Callsite sponsorship — it is referenced by an active hook, rule, or another active skill

If none happens by the deadline, cold-archive it. No "keep in case I need it later."

Active sponsor guards (all must be true):
- Deployed and running (not planned, not paused)
- Documented in the sponsor's manifest or config
- Actually invoked at least once in the window, verifiable via logs

